{{>header}}
	<div id="intro">
		<p>This site was implemented using a combination of Node.js, Express, Handlebars, and good old HTML with a smidgen of CSS.  It's not intended to be pretty (I'm a developer, not a designer), so it's fairly basic.</p>
		<p>Here's the data flow within the application:</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Accept address from the user.</li>
				<li>Send address to MapQuest to retrieve latitude and longitude coordinates.</li>
				<li>Send coordinates from step 2 to DarkSky to retrieve first matching forecast info.</li>
				<li>Format and present basic information from the current conditions.</li>
			</ol>
	</div>
	<div id="form">
		<p>{{message}}</p>
		<form action="/weather">
			<input type="text" name="address"/>
			<button value="Submit" type="submit">Submit</button>
		</form>
	</div>
{{>footer}}